  "summary": "In the morning at the Kurojishi mansion, the narrator reflects on Mutsumi's prediction of a second murder case and his desire to escape the gloomy atmosphere of Kurokawa City. While walking in the corridor, he hears rhythmic hammering and discovers Yamada, a long-term laborer who works at the mansion twice a week, repairing a cracked lily-patterned handrail. Yamada expresses a lack of goodwill toward the sisters Kanae and Miyuki, blaming them for the damage, and voices his fear regarding the unidentified murderer, urging the detective to catch the killer so he can work in peace.\n\nThe atmosphere becomes tense when Keiichiro returns from outside in a bad mood. A confrontation ensues between Keiichiro and Jinma (referred to as Jouma/Jirou), with Jinma defensively claiming he is not \"burying a body.\" Yuzuha intervenes to defend the detective, descending the stairs with Yuki. Amidst the awkward silence, Yuzuha suddenly takes the narrator's hand and leads him outside, an action that leaves both the narrator and a stunned Jinma speechless. After Yuzuha apologizes for her brother's temperament, she shifts the conversation to Mr. Kimitsuki. The narrator agrees with Xuyan's assessment that Kimitsuki is a highly intelligent and capable reasoner, noting that praising a friend is a virtue.",
